- Added Google Cloud Identity Conditional Access integration. Fleet can now write per-host compliance signals into Google Cloud Identity so Workspace admins can gate Workspace and SAML-federated app access on Fleet's view of device state via Context-Aware Access policies. The integration uses the host's hardware serial number plus the Workspace identity signed into Endpoint Verification to resolve the canonical deviceUser, then PATCHes a ClientState with compliance state, managed state, a graduated health score, a human-readable score reason naming any failing CA-flagged policies, and asset tags for the host's team and labels. macOS only in this initial release; Windows and Linux support is plumbed but not yet enabled. See `articles/google-cloud-identity-conditional-access-integration.md` for the setup walkthrough.
